cmrunnwi500019efdijls0kxc	cmprh55jg0000dmaaros54xpj	How many pieces of RDG500/1,25 fit in a 40ft container?	\N	Based on the [MAX CAPACITY RESULT] for RDG500/1,25 in a 40ft container, the maximum number of pieces that can fit is 332,000. This is calculated by fitting 166 crates of type A2 (each containing 2000 pcs), which translates to 332,000 pieces in total.\n\nThis calculation considers the weight as the limiting factor, with a utilization of 99.8% of the container's weight capacity and 23.5% of its volume capacity. Given this high weight utilization, it’s important to monitor the inventory levels of RDG500/1,25 to ensure we can meet such large order demands.\n\nIf you need to ship a similar quantity in the future, make sure to have sufficient crates and raw materials ready well in advance to avoid delays.	t	\N	2026-07-21 12:54:24.843
